5000|$|Tracy Grimshaw, who interviewed Grundy in 2010, said [...] "RG was {{a pioneer}} in game shows, in drama, in <b>soapies.</b> He was a star maker. But he totally {{rejected}} the limelight. He only gave one television interview in his life, and I was privileged and fascinated {{to be the one}} who spoke with him." [...] Grimshaw's interview with Grundy was rebroadcast during the 9 May edition of A Current Affair. Ian Hogg, whose company bought Grundy Organisation, announced that FremantleMedia were thinking of a permanent way to honour Grundy.|$|R
